<section class="section bg-cream">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="section-header centered">
            <span class="section-eyebrow">Why Drip for Alfalfa</span>
            <h2>The Case for SDI in Hay Production</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="three-col-grid">
            <div class="info-card">
                <div class="info-card-icon">💧</div>
                <h3>Harvest Without Delay</h3>
                <p>Flood irrigation requires you to stop irrigating 5–10 days before cutting to firm up the field. Drip lets you irrigate up to 24–48 hours before harvest, maximizing both yield and forage quality.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="info-card">
                <div class="info-card-icon">🧪</div>
                <h3>Fertigation Efficiency</h3>
                <p>Deliver potassium, sulfur, and micronutrients directly to the root zone — not to the field margin. SDI fertigation increases nutrient use efficiency by 40–60% vs. broadcast application.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="info-card">
                <div class="info-card-icon">🌱</div>
                <h3>Stand Longevity</h3>
                <p>Consistent soil moisture from SDI reduces stress cycling and extends stand life — growers regularly achieve 10–12 year productive stands vs. 5–7 years with surface methods.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="info-card">
                <div class="info-card-icon">🚜</div>
                <h3>No Weed Seed Bank Recharge</h3>
                <p>Surface flood irrigation wets the entire field surface, germinating weed seeds with every irrigation. SDI wets only the root zone, dramatically reducing weed pressure between cuttings.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="info-card">
                <div class="info-card-icon">⚡</div>
                <h3>Energy Cost Reduction</h3>
                <p>SDI systems operate at lower pressure than flood-converted sprinkler alternatives. Most alfalfa SDI installations reduce pumping energy costs by 35–55% vs. wheel lines or solid set.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="highlight-card">
                <div class="highlight-card-icon">📊</div>
                <h3>Grower Result</h3>
                <p>A 960-acre alfalfa operation in Nevada reduced water applications from 5.8 to 2.6 acre-feet/acre/year — a $340,000 annual water cost reduction — while increasing cuttings from 7 to 9 per season.</p>
                <a href="/growers-stories" class="btn-primary-sm" style="margin-top:16px;">Read Case Studies →</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

