<section class="section">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="two-col-layout">
            <div>
                <span class="section-eyebrow">System Design</span>
                <h2>SDI for Alfalfa: Design Principles</h2>
                <p>Alfalfa SDI systems use a unique design protocol compared to row crops. Key parameters include:</p>
                <ul class="check-list" style="margin-top:20px;">
                    <li>Lateral spacing: 40–60 inches, installed at 10–14 inches depth</li>
                    <li>Emitter spacing: 12–24 inches depending on soil texture</li>
                    <li>Flow rate: 0.16–0.45 GPH emitters based on infiltration rate</li>
                    <li>Vacuum relief valves at field high points to prevent siphoning</li>
                    <li>Air/vacuum relief at field corners for system protection</li>
                    <li>Chemical injection ports for in-season root intrusion management</li>
                </ul>
                <a href="/agriculture/precision-irrigation" class="btn-primary" style="margin-top:28px;display:inline-block;">Explore Our Technology</a>
            </div>
            <div>
                <div class="info-card" style="margin-bottom:20px;">
                    <h3>🌡️ Recommended Products</h3>
                    <p><strong>DripSmart RootGuard SDI Tape</strong> — Our alfalfa-specific subsurface drip line featuring built-in root barrier for stand longevity. Available in 5/8" and 7/8" diameter.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="info-card">
                    <h3>⚙️ System Integration</h3>
                    <p><strong>DripSphere OS Alfalfa Module</strong> — ET-based alfalfa scheduling integrates with local weather stations and soil moisture sensors to automate irrigation timing around cutting cycles.</p>
                </div>
